Install from pypi with pip
==========================
in a terminal run:

pip install pySPM

Install from github with pip
============================

pip install git+https://github.com/scholi/pySPM@master

Install with git from github
============================
git clone https://github.com/scholi/pySPM
cd pySPM
python setup.py install

Install zip file from github
============================

download : https://github.com/scholi/pySPM/archive/master.zip
unzip file and go inside the pySPM-master folder
run: python setup.py install

Install in edit mode
====================
You might want to get the library and be able to modify it without reinstalling it all the time.
Get a version of pySPM. Either with git or the zipfile from github (see above).
within the pySPM folder run:
pip install -e .

